<p>Most websites publish blog posts at random. A productivity tip on Monday. A product update on Wednesday. A thought leadership piece on Friday. Google indexes all of them and rewards none of them.</p>
<p>That is the core problem. Search engines do not rank individual pages in isolation anymore. They evaluate whether your entire site demonstrates deep, structured expertise on a topic. The sites that build topical authority dominate rankings. Everyone else fights for scraps.</p>
<p>Publishing 25 or more articles within a single content cluster produces a <a href="https://searchengineland.com/guide/topical-authority">40 to 70% increase in keyword rankings</a> within 3 to 6 months. Sites that sustain cluster publishing for 12 or more months see 40% higher organic traffic than those relying on single-page strategies.</p>
<p>We publish 3,500+ blog posts across 70+ industries. Every article we produce fits into a topical cluster. Our average on-page SEO score is 92%. Topical authority is not a theory for us. It is the system we run every day.</p>
<p><strong>Here is what you will learn:</strong></p>
